I made it home.</i>

130
00:07:56,527 --> 00:07:58,109
He doesn't. You're right.

131
00:07:58,145 --> 00:08:00,445
<i>Well, I almost made it home.</i>

132
00:08:00,481 --> 00:08:03,198
Well, as long as it
makes him happy.

133
00:08:03,233 --> 00:08:04,733
Fine with me.

134
00:08:07,454 --> 00:08:09,955
Oh, my God.

135
00:08:09,990 --> 00:08:11,623
Oh, my God!

136
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:14,086
- Jeff.
- Morning.

137
00:08:14,110 --> 00:08:17,445
Jeff. Oh, sweetie!

138
00:08:17,464 --> 00:08:19,581
- Are you okay?
- Mommy.

139
00:08:19,616 --> 00:08:21,478
Oh, sweetie,
what did you do?

140
00:08:21,502 --> 00:08:23,552
I don't think
I got the job, Mommy.

141
00:08:23,587 --> 00:08:25,754
But you know
what still bugs me?

142
00:08:25,789 --> 00:08:28,256
I submit as a fact that
the single hardest thing

143
00:08:28,291 --> 00:08:31,059
for a person with learning
disabilities like mine to do

144
00:08:31,094 --> 00:08:32,427
is to captain a boat.

145
00:08:32,462 --> 00:08:34,657
There's so many things
to take care of.

146
00:08:34,681 --> 00:08:37,465
