00:55:25,573 --> 00:55:28,040
- Get away! Your shoes!
- What's wrong with them?

998
00:55:28,075 --> 00:55:30,520
- Go over there! Please!
- What do you mean?
What's wrong with them?

999
00:55:30,544 --> 00:55:32,461
Take your shoes off.
Throw them over there.

1000
00:55:32,496 --> 00:55:35,998
Oh, my God. Okay.
I'm taking them off.

1001
00:55:37,168 --> 00:55:39,051
Threw 'em away.

1002
00:55:39,086 --> 00:55:41,953
Shh. Try to relax.

1003
00:55:41,972 --> 00:55:44,956
Ohh... Oh, God.

1004
00:55:44,975 --> 00:55:47,559
Just breathe.

1005
00:55:47,595 --> 00:55:51,063
God, Jeff. Shh...

1006
00:55:51,098 --> 00:55:52,348
Your shoes.

1007
00:55:52,400 --> 00:55:53,816
What happened?

1008
00:55:53,851 --> 00:55:55,818
Your shoes are New Balance.

1009
00:55:55,853 --> 00:55:57,269
So?

1010
00:55:59,407 --> 00:56:01,490
I just...

1011
00:56:01,525 --> 00:56:05,494
When I see the word "balance,"
I... I get nauseous,

1012
00:56:05,529 --> 00:56:10,532
and I experience vertigo,
and I just lose my balance.

1013
00:56:10,584 --> 00:56:13,985
It doesn't happen all the time.
It's only when I'm worked up.

1014
00:56:14,004 --> 00:56:15,337
Oh.

1015
00:56:17,007 --> 00:56:19,541
- Oh, God.
- Jeff...

1016
00:56:19,593 --> 00:56:23,629
the sneakers don't even say
the word "balance" on them.

1017
00:56:23,664 --> 00:56:26,215
The "N" is enough.

1018
00:56:28,969 --> 00:56:32,003
I haven't had an episode
like that in a long time.

1019
00:56:32,022 --> 00:56:33,939
I'm okay.

1020
00:56:33,974 --> 00:56:35,557
Thank you.

1021
00:56:35,609 --> 00:56:37,309
Just breathe.

1022
00:56:37,344 --> 00:56:40,562
Careful. Careful.

1023
00:56:42,032 --> 00:56:43,949
God.

1024
00:56:43,984 --> 00:56:46,118
You scared me.

1025
00:56:46,153 --> 00:56:51,990
I mean, Jeff, what happens
if your students wear
New Balance sneakers?

1026
00:56:52,025 --> 00:56:54,376
I ask them to take them off.

1027
00:56:55,529 --> 00:56:58,080
That's so cute.

1028
00:56:58,132 --> 00:57:01,049
Actually, Lynn,
about school...

1029
00:57:01,085 --> 00:57:04,219
I got fired.

1030
00:57:04,255 --> 00:57:09,207
Jeff, how can you
afford that necklace?

1031
00:57:09,226 --> 00:57:11,427
See, that's the best thing.

1032
00:57:11,479 --> 00:57:14,179
Everything's affordable with
Zeffers' new financing plan.

1033
00:57:14,214 --> 00:57:18,434
Jeff, you still have
to pay back the loan.

1034
00:57:18,486 --> 00:57:21,069
I hate to admit it,
but I got you, Lynn.

1035
00:57:21,105 --> 00:57:24,940
I'm going to be
a commercial fisherman,
an old seadog.

1036
00:57:24,992 --> 00:57:28,243
I figured that if this is
a steady thing for me,

1037
00:57:28,279 --> 00:57:32,664
maybe you wouldn't have
to get married to Terry.

1038
00:57:32,700 --> 00:57:37,119
I know this sounds crazy,
but I love you.

1039
00:57:37,171 --> 00:57:39,254
I want to take care of you.

1040
00:57:41,742 --> 00:57:43,575
I love you, too, Jeff.

1041
00:57:43,594 --> 00:57:46,595
You're the best girlfriend
I've ever had.

1042
00:57:46,630 --> 00:57:49,381
The only one, frankly,
but the best.

1043
00:57:49,416 --> 00:57:54,136
You know what?
I don't think I've ever had
a real boyfriend either.

1044
00:57:54,188 --> 00:57:56,021
Just sugar daddies
and pimps?

1045
00:57:58,108 --> 00:57:59,391
Yeah.

1046
00:58:02,730 --> 00:58:06,565
And she says no
because of the mast-head.

1047
00:58:06,600 --> 00:58:07,640
Hmm.

1048
00:58:09,036 --> 00:58:12,321
Hey, Cappy. I'm Jeff.
Sorry I'm late.

1049
00:58:12,373 --> 00:58:13,605
Ease her out there,
Junior.

1050
00:58:13,624 --> 00:58:14,768
You got it, Cap.

1051
00:58:14,792 --> 00:58:16,542
- Where's your gear?
- Gear?

1052
00:58:16,577 --> 00:58:19,161
You don't think this sweater's
gonna be warm enough?

1053
00:58:19,213 --> 00:58:21,257
Yeah, it'll be
warm enough for today,

1054
00:58:21,281 --> 00:58:25,551
but the weather might
get dirty over the next
four to six weeks.

1055
00:58:25,586 --> 00:58:30,556
And even though I made
a little mistake by boarding
a month-long cruise,

1056
00:58:30,591 --> 00:58:34,142
being aboard a boat without
having the responsibility
of captaining it

1057
00:58:34,178 --> 00:58:38,430
was gonna be like
playing the lotto without
having to buy the tickets.

1058
00:58:38,465 --> 00:58:40,432
<i>It was going to be heaven.</i>

1059
00:58:40,467 --> 00:58:44,069
<i>And while we steamed into it,
all I thought about was Lynn</i>

1060
00:58:44,104 --> 00:58:47,138
<i>lying in bed, watching reruns
of the Luggage Channel.</i>

1061
00:58:47,157 --> 00:58:51,026
<i>With this peerless
Cincinnati Sateen rolling bag,</i>

1062
00:58:51,078 --> 00:58:54,613
<i>you'll be the toast
of high tea in London.</i>

1063
00:59:01,839 --> 00:59:05,507
<i>And thanks to this patented
tri-fold center strap,</i>

1064
00:59:05,543 --> 00:59:07,543
<i>when you land in Dubai,</i>

1065
00:59:07,595 --> 00:59:09,661
<i>say bye-bye to creases
in your clothing.</i>

1066
00:59:09,680 --> 00:59:14,433
<i>And now for</i>
<i>my favorite feature,</i>
<i>the snap pocket.</i>

1067
00:59:17,638 --> 00:59:23,275
Junior,
get fuckin' Santa's helper
to lift the fuckin' nets out!

1068
00:59:23,310 --> 00:59:25,844
Dipshit, give me a fuckin' hand!

1069
00:59:25,863 --> 00:59:29,180
- All right.
- Hold onto that.

1070
00:59:29,199 --> 00:59:30,449
Tight!

1071
00:59:34,204 --> 00:59:38,073
Right,
when I say when, pull.

1072
00:59:38,125 --> 00:59:39,458
What?

1073
00:59:39,493 --> 00:59:42,377
When I...
When I say when, pull.

1074
00:59:42,413 --> 00:59:44,413
I already am pulling on it.

1075
00:59:44,465 --> 00:59:46,748
Just... You know what?
Don't pull.

1076
00:59:46,800 --> 00:59:48,533
I don't need your help.
Go. Go.

1077
00:59:48,552 --> 00:59:50,113
You need a spotter
or something?

1078
00:59:50,137 --> 00:59:52,554
No, I don't need a spotter.
Fuck, man.

1079
00:59:52,590 --> 00:59:54,723
Get the fuck out of here.
A spotter!

1080
00:59:58,378 --> 01:00:00,178
Morning, Cappy.

1081
01:00:02,182 --> 01:00:03,682
Man the wheel.

1082
01:00:03,717 --> 01:00:05,462
I don't think
that's a good idea.

1083
01:00:05,486 --> 01:00:06,796
I've sunk
one of these before.

1084
01:00:06,820 --> 01:00:08,465
- You've what?
- I sunk one.

1085
01:00:08,489 --> 01:00:09,404
Just go.

1086
01:00:09,440 --> 01:00:10,772
Go, go. Get Junior.

1087
01:00:10,824 --> 01:00:13,344
Tell him I need
a man up here.

1088
01:00:16,396 --> 01:00:18,830
These nets
look different.

1089
01:00:18,866 --> 01:00:22,284
Yeah. It's 'cause
we're going for weak fish.

1090
01:00:22,336 --> 01:00:23,585
Weak fish?

1091
01:00:23,621 --> 01:00:26,288
The small white ones.
Use them as bait.

1092
01:00:26,340 --> 01:00:27,756
Nothing, right?

1093
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:30,125
You're such a fuckin' idiot.

1094
01:00:30,177 --> 01:00:31,409
Get a wrench
and help me out.

1095
01:00:31,428 --> 01:00:33,411
Okay.

1096
01:00:33,430 --> 01:00:35,191
Come on, princess,
bring it up.

1097
01:00:35,215 --> 01:00:39,751
Come on, give it some gas!
Get the whip line.

1098
01:00:39,770 --> 01:00:42,604
You see, when you're netting
for a particular kind of fish

1099
01:00:42,640 --> 01:00:45,390
and one that may not already
be in danger of being wiped out,

1100
01:00:45,425 --> 01:00:47,442
you inevitably scoop up
those that are.

1101
01:00:47,478 --> 01:00:49,194
<i>It's called a by catch.</i>

1102
01:00:49,229 --> 01:00:50,469
It's coming.

1103
01:00:52,933 --> 01:00:55,867
<i>I spent my whole life trying
to catch fish like this.</i>

1104
01:00:55,903 --> 01:00:59,321
<i>We're talking about Spanish
mackerel, porgies, tuna,</i>

1105
01:00:59,373 --> 01:01:03,158
<i>and the most amazing and
beautiful sport fish of all...</i>

1106
01:01:03,210 --> 01:01:05,460
<i>The striped bass.</i>

1107
01:01:05,496 --> 01:01:07,612
<i>We struck gold.</i>

1108
01:01:07,631 --> 01:01:10,499
<i>It was the kind of gold
you had to throw back.</i>

1109
01:01:15,756 --> 01:01:18,306
- What the hell are you doing?
- What the fuck, man!

1110
01:01:18,342 --> 01:01:20,203
I'm throwing them back,
Cappy. They're beautiful.

1111
01:01:20,227 --> 01:01:21,476
And they're dying.

1112
01:01:21,512 --> 01:01:22,678
What the fuck!

1113
01:01:22,730 --> 01:01:24,491
Listen, Cappy,
I may not know much,

1114
01:01:24,515 --> 01:01:26,609
but I know it's illegal to
net for these kind of fish.

1115
01:01:26,633 --> 01:01:28,767
We'll throw them back later.

1116
01:01:28,802 --> 01:01:30,580
But, Cappy, you'll be
throwing them back dead.

1117
01:01:30,604 --> 01:01:32,637
I said we'll
throw them back later!

1118
01:01:32,656 --> 01:01:36,241
Now, every fuckin fish that
swims by here right now,

1119
01:01:36,276 --> 01:01:39,361
that's 3.25 to the pound
that I'm losing!

1120
01:01:39,413 --> 01:01:41,863
Now, I'm going to give you
to the count of three

1121
01:01:41,915 --> 01:01:46,785
to get the goddamn nets
back out!

1122
01:01:46,820 --> 01:01:48,503
One, two...

1123
01:01:48,539 --> 01:01:51,289
Okay, okay.

1124
01:01:53,794 --> 01:01:58,296
<i>Now, I am no great
environmentalist, okay?</i>

1125
01:01:58,331 --> 01:01:59,848
Hell, I don't even recycle.

1126
01:01:59,883 --> 01:02:03,969
But what Al was proposing
was murdering all these fish.

1127
01:02:10,677 --> 01:02:12,360
No! No! No! No!

1128
01:02:12,396 --> 01:02:14,679
I'm not going to let you
bastards get away with this.

1129
01:02:14,698 --> 01:02:16,458
You're going
to have to kill me

1130
01:02:16,483 --> 01:02:19,017
before I let these fish
suffocate on deck.

1131
01:02:19,036 --> 01:02:20,852
It's either me
or the fish, gentlemen.

1132
01:02:20,871 --> 01:02:26,825
But I swear, I will gut you
before you get me overboard.

1133
01:02:26,860 --> 01:02:30,829
All I'm asking is you let me
throw these fish back

1134
01:02:30,864 --> 01:02:32,842
before you throw
your stinking nets out there.

1135
01:02:32,866 --> 01:02:35,467
It'll only take a minute.
How's it going to go down?

1136
01:02:35,502 --> 01:02:38,253
This is mutiny, faggy.

1137
01:02:38,305 --> 01:02:39,888
You lose your quarter share.

1138
01:02:39,923 --> 01:02:41,339
So be it.

1139
01:02:41,374 --> 01:02:44,893
Junior, get back on the crane.

1140
01:02:52,352 --> 01:02:53,985
Go ahead.

1141
01:02:55,355 --> 01:02:57,751
You're in such
a world of shit.

1142
01:02:57,775 --> 01:02:59,324
It's my world.

1143
01:02:59,359 --> 01:03:01,805
Tell me when
you find Nemo.

1144
01:03:01,829 --> 01:03:04,996
What I didn't figure
into my mutiny was...

1145
01:03:05,032 --> 01:03:06,976
<i>now I was going to be
at sea for three weeks</i>

1146
01:03:07,000 --> 01:03:09,718
<i>with people who
wanted to kill me.</i>

1147
01:03:09,753 --> 01:03:12,521
<i>People die at sea
all the time.</i>

1148
01:03:12,556 --> 01:03:15,323
<i>It didn't matter.
Neither the threat of death</i>

1149
01:03:15,359 --> 01:03:17,270
<i>or the loss of money
mattered at all to me</i>

1150
01:03:17,294 --> 01:03:18,972
<i>because I knew that
as soon as I got home,</i>

1151
01:03:18,996 --> 01:03:21,696
<i>I would have Lynn there
waiting for me.</i>

1152
01:03:33,393 --> 01:03:36,311
It says there's
a tropical storm
off the coast.

1153
01:03:36,363 --> 01:03:38,563
Yeah, I read that, too.

1154
01:03:38,598 --> 01:03:40,982
It's supposed to be
40-knot winds.

1155
01:03:41,034 --> 01:03:43,869
Do you think it'd be safe
to be on a boat?

1156
01:03:43,904 --> 01:03:47,072
I sure as hell wouldn't
want to be on one.

1157
01:03:55,448 --> 01:03:57,716
You expecting someone?

1158
01:04:11,598 --> 01:04:13,765
- Yes?
- Are you Lynn Ferguson?

1159
01:04:13,800 --> 01:04:14,950
I am.

1160
01:04:14,985 --> 01:04:17,635
Hi, Miss Ferguson.
Sorry to bother you.

1161
01:04:17,654 --> 01:04:19,048
We have a judgment
against Jeff Nichols,

1162
01:04:19,072 --> 01:04:22,023
and he listed this
as his primary address.

1163
01:04:22,075 --> 01:04:26,862
Me and my friend Peanut
are here to repossess
that diamond necklace.

1164
01:04:30,751 --> 01:04:33,418
Uh, I'll go grab the box.

1165
01:04:42,713 --> 01:04:44,691
May I ask you
what is this about?

1166
01:04:44,715 --> 01:04:47,382
Well, grandpa,
looks like some loverboy

1167
01:04:47,417 --> 01:04:50,552
bought your daughter
a necklace he couldn't afford.

1168
01:04:55,175 --> 01:04:56,775
Thank you.

1169
01:05:07,905 --> 01:05:11,039
I... I can't wait to see her.

1170
01:05:11,074 --> 01:05:15,160
In fact, does anyone know
where there's a good florist?

1171
01:05:15,195 --> 01:05:16,711
Whoa.

1172
01:05:16,747 --> 01:05:18,797
Thanks for letting me share.

1173
01:05:18,832 --> 01:05:20,498
Thanks, Jeff.

1174
01:05:35,649 --> 01:05:37,983
Lynn!

1175
01:05:41,888 --> 01:05:43,688
Wait. Wait, wait!

1176
01:05:43,723 --> 01:05:46,191
Wait! Why are you running?

1177
01:05:48,695 --> 01:05:49,861
Lynn!

1178
01:05:52,065 --> 01:05:54,499
Wait.

1179
01:05:54,534 --> 01:05:56,584
Wait.

1180
01:05:56,620 --> 01:05:58,870
Give me a moment.

1181
01:05:58,905 --> 01:06:00,705
I just got back.

1182
01:06:00,757 --> 01:06:04,575
I went to a quick meeting,
but then I came straight here.

1183
01:06:04,594 --> 01:06:07,963
They didn't have
a phone on the boat.

1184
01:06:08,966 --> 01:06:12,217
I've missed you so much.

1185
01:06:14,972 --> 01:06:17,212
Why aren't you wearing
your necklace?

1186
01:06:20,560 --> 01:06:22,477
It's over, Jeff.

1187
01:06:22,529 --> 01:06:23,645
Over!

1188
01:06:23,697 --> 01:06:25,647
Wait.

1189
01:06:25,699 --> 01:06:30,201
Do you mean it's over
between you and Terry
or you and me?

1190
01:06:41,298 --> 01:06:45,050
You can't go.
I've got my six-month
anniversary coming up.

1191
01:06:45,085 --> 01:06:48,219
Yeah. Well,
I got my 10-year
anniversary coming up.

1192
01:06:48,255 --> 01:06:51,256
What have I done
with my time? Nothing.

1193
01:06:51,291 --> 01:06:53,508
I need help, Lenny.

1194
01:06:53,560 --> 01:06:56,627
I just lost
the love of my life
due to poor accounting,

1195
01:06:56,646 --> 01:06:57,707
I'm here. I'll help you.

1196
01:06:57,731 --> 01:06:58,847
I got a new tactic.

1197
01:06:58,899 --> 01:07:00,598
It's called surrender.

1198
01:07:00,633 --> 01:07:04,302
See, me and details, we went
to battle three decades ago,

1199
01:07:04,321 --> 01:07:08,106
and I can honestly say
that that war is over,
and I've lost.

1200
01:07:08,141 --> 01:07:10,692
So you're just
going to be a bum?

1201
01:07:10,744 --> 01:07:14,112
I'm retiring. Mike's brother has
got a garage apartment in Quogue

1202
01:07:14,147 --> 01:07:15,580
he's going to rent me
real cheap.

1203
01:07:15,615 --> 01:07:18,166
I got all I need right here.

1204
01:07:18,201 --> 01:07:20,952
Okay, retire,
but promise me one thing.

1205
01:07:20,987 --> 01:07:22,631
You'll keep going
to meetings

1206
01:07:22,655 --> 01:07:24,917
'cause those people need you
as much as you need them.

1207
01:07:24,941 --> 01:07:27,876
Lenny, how can I expect
other people to be
interested in my problems

1208
01:07:27,911 --> 01:07:29,794
when they don't even
impress me?

1209
01:07:29,829 --> 01:07:33,014
I have learning disabilities,
and I drank a lot
when I was a kid.

1210
01:07:33,050 --> 01:07:34,933
It's like having gingivitis,
you know?

1211
01:07:34,968 --> 01:07:36,601
Buy a toothbrush,
get on with it.

1212
01:07:36,636 --> 01:07:39,054
I cannot believe
I'm hearing you say this.

1213
01:07:40,173 --> 01:07:42,857
I'm sorry to disappoint you,
Lenny.

1214
01:07:42,893 --> 01:07:45,143
It was good knowing you, man.
Don't drink.

1215
01:07:59,793 --> 01:08:01,076
Hey, Jeff!

1216
01:08:01,128 --> 01:08:02,911
Hey, Uncle Popcorn.

1217
01:08:02,963 --> 01:08:04,796
- How you doing?
- I'm good.

1218
01:08:04,831 --> 01:08:06,642
Don't call me
Uncle Popcorn, okay?

1219
01:08:06,666 --> 01:08:07,865
Yeah, sure.

1220
01:08:07,884 --> 01:08:09,867
- Give me that.
- Okay. All right.

1221
01:08:09,886 --> 01:08:12,837
Hey, all this is yours, man,
any time you want to use it.

1222
01:08:12,872 --> 01:08:14,016
You know how to use
this thing here?

1223
01:08:14,040 --> 01:08:15,039
Not really.

1224
01:08:15,058 --> 01:08:17,175
Let me show you.
It's easy.

1225
01:08:17,210 --> 01:08:20,595
Step up, step up, and ho!

1226
01:08:20,647 --> 01:08:21,707
- Wow!
- Ho!

1227
01:08:21,731 --> 01:08:23,815
All right!

1228
01:08:23,850 --> 01:08:27,318
Okay? Give it a try.
Come on.

1229
01:08:29,356 --> 01:08:31,906
That's it.

1230
01:08:31,942 --> 01:08:33,224
Ah, it's all right.
It's all right.

1231
01:08:33,243 --> 01:08:36,277
- No, no, that ain't the way.
- Okay.

1232
01:08:36,329 --> 01:08:39,030
- All right, let's go.
- Sorry.

1233
01:08:39,065 --> 01:08:41,616
Don't use that
until I show you how.

1234
01:08:41,668 --> 01:08:44,085
And my barbeque here?
You don't fuckin' touch that.

